# Resources blog — long-form template (standard)

Use this for new guides under `/resources/blog/` so they match **University of Florida Online 2026** and **Online college enrollment after the pandemic**: same chrome, spacing, TOC, and sidebar.

## Required shell

1. **`ResourcesGuideLayout`** from `src/components/blog/ResourcesGuideLayout.astro` — not `BlogArticleLayout`, not raw `Layout` for full articles.
2. **Body** wrapped in **`ArticleProse`** when the article is authored as HTML in the page (`.astro`). For MDX from `src/content/blog/`, keep the thin route page that imports `ResourcesGuideLayout` + `getEntry` + `<Content />` (see `university-of-florida-online-2026-guide.astro`).

## Props checklist

- **`canonical`**: path only, e.g. `/resources/blog/my-slug`
- **`image`**: OG hero image (absolute URL or site path)
- **`categoryLabel`**, **`breadcrumbTitle`** (short crumb), **`author`**, **`authorTitle`**, **`readingTime`**, **`updatedDate`** (display string), **`tags`**
- **`tocItems`**: `ResourcesGuideTocItem[]` with **`{ href: '#section-id', label: '…' }`** (numbered TOC + anchor jumps)
- **`sidebarCta`** (optional but default for guides): same pattern as UF — e.g. intro + `/colleges` + “College guides →” unless the post needs a different CTA

## JSON-LD

Put scripts in **`<script type="application/ld+json" slot="head" … />`** so structured data lives in `<head>`.

## Body styling

Rely on **`ArticleProse`** + shared prose utilities (`summary-box`, `link-external`, FAQ blocks). Heading hover and link behavior are aligned with **`ResourcesGuideLayout`** global `.article-content` rules.

## Do not

- Introduce a second “blog article” shell for new `/resources/blog/*` pages without team agreement.
- Drop `ArticleProse` for long guides unless the content is pure MDX rendered without the wrapper (MDX route then uses layout-only styles from `ResourcesGuideLayout`).
